            My comparison with Northern Ireland showed that arrangements on equality and human rights are in place so that the identity and rights of people of all backgrounds&#x2014;not just those of nationalists, Catholics, Unionists or Protestants&#x2014;are protected, overseen and looked after. Any negotiated settlement could and would address such issues in a way that suits everyone. I make that point not to offer a particular solution but to suggest a process similar, but not the same, to that in Northern Ireland&#x2014;I accept the distinction made by the hon. Member for Romford (Mr. Rosindell) in his intervention&#x2014;
          </p>
